        <updateDate>2021-03-25T02:16:28Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Grand Canyon Protection Act</b></p> <p>This bill withdraws 1,006,545 acres of federal lands in Arizona, including any land or interest in land acquired by the United States after enactment of this bill, from </p> <ul> <li>entry, appropriation, and disposal under the public land laws; </li> <li>location, entry, and patent under the mining laws; and </li> <li>operation of the mineral leasing and geothermal leasing laws and mineral materials laws. </li> </ul> <p>The Government Accountability Office shall conduct a study of uranium stockpiles in the United States that are available to meet future national security requirements.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
